  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Product Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>What we are looking for:</strong></p><p><strong>Experience & Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma/Degree in Computer Science, IT, Engineering or related field</li><li>Minimum 5 years of relevant experience in product management, with preference for AI/data product experience</li><li>Experience working directly with data scientists, AI/ML engineers, designers, and product teams</li><li>Strong background in modern AI/data development practices (Agile, AWS Cloud, Cloud AI services, Data Engineering, Design Thinking)</li><li>Proven track record of shipping successful AI or data products from scratch</li></ul><p><strong>Technical Skills</strong></p><ul><li>AI/ML product and project management</li><li>Strong analytical and problem-solving capabilities with data-driven approaches</li><li>Understanding of machine learning workflows, data pipelines, and AI model deployment</li><li>User experience (UX) capabilities</li></ul><p><strong>Professional Attributes:</strong></p><ul><li>Familiarity with IM8 policies, GCC architecture, CI/CD pipelines</li><li>Strategic thinking and decision-making ability in AI and data contexts</li><li>Excellence in stakeholder management and communication across technical and non-technical audiences</li><li>Data-driven approach to problem-solving</li></ul><p><strong>Personal Qualities</strong></p><ul><li>Action-oriented mindset with focus on AI innovation</li><li>Innovation-focused approach</li><li>Growth mindset and continuous learning attitude towards emerging AI technologies</li><li>Strong sense of ownership and accountability</li><li>Passion for heritage preservation and leveraging technology for societal benefit</li></ul>",
